FARMERS’ & MECHANICS’ NAT. BANK OF FORT WORTH, Tex., Petitioner, v. W. W. WILKINSON, Trustee, Respondent. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. January 24, 1925.) No. 4378. J. A. Templeton, of Fort Worth, Tex., G. A. Stultz, of Wichita, Kan., Clay Cooke, of Fort Worth, Tex., and W. E. Spell, of Waco, Tex., for petitioner. Stanley Boykin and H. C. Ray, both of Fort Worth, Tex. (C. M. Conner and Capps, Cantey, Hanger So Short, all of Fort Worth, Tex., and Orestes Mitchell, of St. Joseph, Mo., on the brief), for respondent.

Before WALKER and BRYAN, Circuit Judges, and DAWKINS, District Judge.

BRYAN, Circuit Judge.

Applying the decision this day announced in the ease of W. W. Wilkinson, Trustee, v. J. L. Walker (No. 4346) 3 F.(2d) 872, the petition to superintend and revise in this case is denied.
